# Supabase Patterns

## Clients

- Browser auth/forms: `createClient()` from `src/lib/supabase/client.ts`
- Server Components & Server Actions: `createClient()` from `src/lib/supabase/server.ts`
- Route protection: `src/middleware.ts` via `updateSession`

## Security

- RLS is the primary authorization layer — do not bypass with service role in app code
- Admin writes require `profiles.role = 'admin'` (checked by RLS and `requireAdmin()`)
- Service role key is only for `scripts/seed-admin.mjs`, never in the Next.js app

## Schema

- Migrations in `supabase/migrations/`
- Order snapshots store drink/add-on names and prices at submit time
- New auth users get `profiles.role = 'user'` via trigger
